obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line 4
  line `THE TRANSFER OF PRISONERS ACT, 1950`
  line `A CT N O. 29 OF 1950 1`
  line `[12 th April, 1950. ]`
  line `An Act to provide for the removal from one State to another of persons confined in a prison.`
  line `B E it en acted by Parliament as follows: —`
  line `1. Short title and extent. — ( 1 ) This Act may be called the Transfer of Prisoners Act, 1950.`
  line `( 2 ) It extends to the whole of India 2 * * *.`
  line `2. Definitions. — In this Act, —`
  line `( a ) “ court ” includes any officer lawfully exercising civil, c riminal or revenue jurisdiction;`
  line `3 [( b ) “ Government ” or “ State Government ”, in relation to a Part C State, means the administrator`
  line `thereof; ]`
  line `( c ) “ prison ” includes any place which has been declared by State Government, by general or`
  line `special order, to be a subsidiary jail.`
  line `3. Removal of prisoners from one State t o another. — ( 1 ) Where any person is c onfined in a prison`
  line `in a State, —`
  line `( a ) under sentence of death, or`
  line `( b ) under, or in lieu of, a sentence of imp risonment or transportation, or`
  line `( c ) in d efault of payment of a fine, or`
  line `( d ) in default of giving security for keeping the peace or for maintaining good behaviour;`
  line `the Government of that State may, with the consent of the Government of any other State, by order,`
  line `provide for the removal of the prisoner from that prison to any prison in the other State.`
  line `( 2 ) The officer in charge of the prison to which any person is removed under sub - section ( 1 ) shall`
  line `receive and detain him, so far as may be, according to the exigency of any writ, warrant or order of the`
  line `court by which such person has been committed, or until such person is discharged or removed in due`
  line `course of law.`
  line `4. [ Amendment of section 29, Act III of 1900.] Rep. by the Repealing and Amending Act, 195 7`
  line `(36 of 1957), s. 2 and Sch. I.`
  line `1. The Act has been extended to —`
  line `Kohima and Mokakchung Districts by Reg. 7 of 1961;`
  line `Dadra and Nagar Haveli by Reg. 6 of 1963;`
  line `Goa, Daman and Diu by notification No. GSR 430, dated 9 - 3 - 1965, see Gazette of India, Part II, s. 3( i ).`
  line `2. The words “extends to the State of Jammu and Kashmir” omitted by Act 25 of 1968, s. 2 and the Sch. (w.e.f. 15 - 8 - 1968).`
  line `3. Subs. by A.O. (No. 3) 1956, for cl. ( b ) (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
