  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  sourcePage 5
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line 5
  line `STATEMENT OF OBJECTS AND REASONS`
  line `Section 29 of the Prisoners’ Act, 1900, inter alia provides for the inter State transfer of prisoners`
  line `between the States in Parts A, C and D of the First Schedule to the Constitution. There is no provision`
  line `however, either in the Prisoners’ Act, 1900, or any other law for transfer of prisoners from prisons in`
  line `those States to prisons in Part B States and vice versa. Cases may arise where the removal or transfer of`
  line `prisoners from Parts A, C and D States to Part B States and vice versa, may be considered`
  line `administratively desirable or necessary.`
  line `This Bill is intended to provide legal sanction for such transfer or removals.`
  line `N EW D ELHI; VALLABHBHAI PATEL.`
  line `The 27 th Februar y, 1950.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
